$ Oracle: Memory
@ memory

Memory which is used for Oracle can be roughly divided into
table { ll
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA ☰ Instance - data that is shared among processes/database users (such as buffer cache, shared pool and redo log buffer)
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA ☰ The exclusive (non-shared) amount of memory used by each  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes (Foreground and → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes/background[background]) has its own exclusive (non-shared).
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/UGA ☰ → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/session[Sessions]
  CGA ☰ Used during a call
table }

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/memory-management[Memory management]

